Claude automatically discovers and uses MCP tools
When Claude Desktop starts up, it reads your claude_desktop_config.json and launches all the MCP servers listed there. It then asks each server "what tools do you have?" — and your weather server responds with two tools: get_alerts and get_forecast.
From that point on, Claude knows those tools exist and what they do — because of the descriptions you wrote in the code:
python@mcp.tool()
async def get_forecast(latitude: float, longitude: float) -> str:
    """Get weather forecast for a location."""  # ← Claude reads this


The config file tells Claude Desktop which servers to run. The docstrings in your code tell Claude what each tool does. Claude's AI then decides on its own when it's appropriate to call those tools — just like it decides when to search the web.


